"content": "<p>A term used in the NT to refer to the place in which departed spirits rest, while waiting for judgment.</p>\n<h2>Hades is the place where the dead wait for judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:13-Rev20:14\">REV 20:13–20:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:23\">MAT 11:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:15\">LUK 10:15</a> <em>translated “depths”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:23\">LUK 16:23</a> <em>translated “hell”</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:27\">ACT 2:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:31\">ACT 2:31</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:8\">REV 6:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is Lord of Hades</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:18\">MAT 16:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a></strong></p>",
